Jail says he is pleased to have signed for the 2016 African Champions and reigning PSL champions. JOHANNESBURG - Mamelodi Sundowns have completed the signing of former Orlando Pirates and KV Oostende midfielder Andile Jali, the club announced on Friday. Jali returned from Belgian after spending four and a half years at KV Oostende and there has been much speculation since his arrival back to South Africa that he would join one of the countries top three PSL sides. It was speculated that Kaizer Chiefs, his old club, Orlando Pirates and Sundowns were in the running to secure his services for the next PSL season. Jail says he is pleased to have signed for the 2016 African Champions and reigning PSL champions. “At last, this deal is done. It’s been a long process but I’m relieved and I can relax before the season starts.” 